branchCategory.name: XL
branchCategory.description: <p>High vacuum angle valve series XL provides excellent thermal conductivity results in a uniform temperature for the entire valve body and a marked decrease in the condensation of gases inside the valve. The valve does not contain heavy metals such as Ni (nickel) or Cr (chrome) and a low sputtering yield also helps to minimize heavy metal contamination of semiconductor wafers.</p>

branchItem.name: XLA, Aluminum High Vacuum Angle Valve, Normally Closed/Bellows Seal
branchItem.description: <p>Series XLA are high vacuum angle valves for use in industrial applications employing high vacuum and process gases. &nbsp;Common industries that may use these angle valves include semiconductor, solar and other electonics production, as well as food and pharmaceutical manufacturing. &nbsp;XLA valves are single-acting, normally closed, with a bellows seal over the shaft and spring. &nbsp;The vavle opens when pressure is applied at the pilot port. &nbsp;The bellows assembly can be replaced, reducing maintenance costs and waste materials. &nbsp;The valve body is hard anodized A6063 aluminum, with 304 stainless steel valves and bellows. &nbsp;Numerous seal materials are available for a wide range of chmical compatibility.</p>

branchItem.description: <p>Series XLAV is a high vacuum angle valve for use in industrial applications employing high vacuum and process gases. &nbsp;Common industries that may use these angle valves include semiconductor, solar and other electronics production, as well as food and pharmaceutical manufacturing. &nbsp;XLAV valves are single-acting, normally closed, with a bellows seal over the shaft and spring. &nbsp;The bellows assembly can be replaced, reducing maintenance costs and waste materials.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>

branchItem.name: XLC, Aluminum High Vacuum Angle Valve, Double Acting, Bellows Seal
branchItem.description: <p>XLC is a double acting high vacuum angle valve with a bellows seal for the shaft. The XL* family shares common features with all series members. Bodies are made of aluminum for lightweight and excellent thermal conductivity, resulting in a uniform temperature for the entire valve body. The body offers excellent resistance to fluorine corrosion. A low sputtering yield and the absence of heavy metals avoid wafer contamination.</p>
branchItem.bullets: <UL> <LI>Air pressure applied to pilot port shifts piston-coupled valve <LI>Replaceable bellows reduces maintenance cost and waste material <LI>Additional maintenance parts available to extend useful life of valve <LI>Standard FKM seals, plus 8 additional seal compound options <LI>Auto switches mountable from 4 directions <LI>Optional 100°C and 150°C heaters (UL compliant lead wire) </LI></UL>

branchItem.name: XLFV, Aluminum High Vacuum Angle Valve, Normally Closed, O-ring Seal with Solenoid Valve
branchItem.description: <p>Series XLFV is a high vacuum angle valve for use in industrial applications employing high vacuum and process gases.&nbsp; Common industries that may use this angle valve include semiconductor, solar and other electronics production, as well as food and pharmaceutical manufacturing.&nbsp; The XLFV valves are single-acting, normally closed.&nbsp; The spring an shaft are exposed to gas flow, but a scraper and O-ring seal the piston pressure volume from process gases.&nbsp; The XLFV opens when pressure is applied at the pilot port, which is controlled by a body mounted solenoid valve.&nbsp; The valve body is hard anodized A6063 aluminum, with 304 stainless steel valves and an electroless nickel plated steel spring.&nbsp; The XLFV bellows are 316L stainless steel.&nbsp; Numerous seal material are available for a wide range of chemical compatibility.</p>
